In PR #5967, I removed the duplicate codes in the `removeUnixSocketSuccess` case.
This is a continuation of that.

---
For example, tests like the following:

```typescript
unitTest({ perms: { read: true, write: true } }, function removeDirSyncSuccess(): void {
  ... SETUP ...
  Deno.removeSync(path);
  ... ASSERTION ...
});

unitTest({ perms: { read: true, write: true } }, async function removeDirSuccess(): Promise<void> {
  ... SETUP ...
  await Deno.remove(path);
  ... ASSERTION ...
});
```

are merged into:

```typescript
const REMOVE_METHODS = ["remove", "removeSync"];
unitTest({ perms: { read: true, write: true } }, async function removeDirSuccess(): Promise<void> {
  for (const method of REMOVE_METHODS) {
    ... SETUP ...
    await Deno[method](path);
    ... ASSERTION ...
  }
});
```

This reiterated pull request fixes issue #5653 about the console log not aligning.
The indentations have been fixed.
Somehow writing `level + 1` instead of `level` somewhere was messing up everything.

